'''The Kin''' is a {{2|Bosses|Boss}} encounter found in the {{2|Overgrowth}}. The fight consists of two {{M|Kin Follower||2}}s and one {{M|Kin Priest||2}}.

== Kin Priest ==
{{Enemy Infobox|Kin Priest|2}}
=== Pattern ===
{{Intents|Kin Priest|2}}
The Kin Priest cycles through four moves in a fixed order:
# {{Int|Kin Priest|Orb of Frailty||2}}
# {{Int|Kin Priest|Orb of Weakness||2}}
# {{Int|Kin Priest|Soul Beam||2}}
# {{Int|Kin Priest|Dark Ritual||2}}

{{Clear}}

== Kin Follower ==
{{Enemy Infobox|Kin Follower|2}} {{Power Infobox|Minion|2}}
=== Pattern ===
{{Intents|Kin Follower|2}}
Each Kin Follower cycles through three moves in a fixed order:
# {{Int|Kin Follower|Quick Slash||2}}
# {{Int|Kin Follower|Boomerang||2}}
# {{Int|Kin Follower|Power Dance||2}}

The two Kin Followers start offset from each other: one begins with {{Int|Kin Follower|Quick Slash||2}} and the other begins with {{Int|Kin Follower|Power Dance||2}}.

{{Clear}}

== Notes ==
* When both Kin Followers are killed, the Kin Priest has a dialogue reaction, but the fight continues normally.
* Both Kin Followers and the Kin Priest gain {{BD|Strength||2}} through their buff moves ({{Int|Kin Follower|Power Dance||2}} and {{Int|Kin Priest|Dark Ritual||2}}), so the encounter's damage output scales over time.
* {{Int|Kin Priest|Orb of Frailty||2}} applies {{BD|Frail||2}}, reducing your block gained by 25%. {{Int|Kin Priest|Orb of Weakness||2}} applies {{BD|Weak||2}}, reducing your attack damage by 25%.

== Trivia ==
* A Kin Follower appears in {{C|Suppress||2}}'s card art, being held by the {{KW|Silent||2}}.

